1. Check the backend is working
Open your browser and go to:


http://localhost:5000/health
You should see:


{"status":"ok","service":"proctoring-backend","timestamp":"..."}
If you see that — backend is alive.

2. Check frontend and backend are connected
Go to http://localhost:3000 in your browser and try to log in with:

Registration No: T22-03-04321
Password: Password123!
If it works (takes you to the dashboard) → they are connected.

If you see a red error message → they are not connected. The most common reason is the backend isn't running.

3. Quick visual checklist
Check	How	Expected result
Backend alive	Visit http://localhost:5000/health	JSON with "status":"ok"
Database connected	Visit http://localhost:5000/health (same page)	No error in backend terminal
Frontend running	Visit http://localhost:3000	Login page loads
Connected	Log in on the login page	Goes to dashboard
4. Watch the backend terminal while you use the site
When you click anything on the frontend, you should see logs appear in the backend PowerShell window like:


[INFO] POST /api/auth/login
[INFO] GET /api/exams
If you see these logs when you click — they are connected.